  <refnamediv>
    <refname>ld_AndroidSensors</refname>

    <refpurpose> Read out Android Sensors and synchronise the simulation to them</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>[sim, out, SensorID] = ld_AndroidSensors(sim, events, in, ConfigStruct)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para><para></para>
<para> Special: SYNC_BLOCK (use only one block of this type in an asynchronous running sub-simulation)</para>
<para></para>
<para> out - vector of size 10 containing the sensor values</para>
<para> in - when in becomes one, the synchronisation loop is interrupted</para>
<para> SensorID - The ID of the sensor that send new data</para>
<para> </para>
<para> Possible sensor ID&amp;apos;s:</para>
<para> </para>
<para>     ASENSOR_TYPE_ACCELEROMETER      = 1,</para>
<para>     ASENSOR_TYPE_MAGNETIC_FIELD     = 2,</para>
<para>     ASENSOR_TYPE_GYROSCOPE          = 4,</para>
<para>     ASENSOR_TYPE_LIGHT              = 5,</para>
<para>     ASENSOR_TYPE_PROXIMITY          = 8</para>
<para> </para>
<para> EXPERIMENTAL</para>
<para> </para>
</para>

    
  </refsection>


